article.description: — Malachi Smith scored 24 points and Chattanooga beat Wofford 75-67 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Smith scores 24 to lift Chattanooga past Wofford 75-67
article.linkText: Smith scores 24 to lift Chattanooga past Wofford 75-67
article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. -- — Malachi Smith scored 24 points and Chattanooga beat Wofford 75-67 on Wednesday night. David Jean-Baptiste had 17 points for Chattanooga and Darius Banks scored 12 for the Mocs (12-3, 2-0 Southern Conference). Max Klesmit scored 22 points, Sam Godwin 17 and B.J. Mack 10 for the Terriers (8-6, 0-2). ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
